WEBVTT

00:00.220 --> 00:02.048
<i>Previously on "Legends"...</i>

00:02.049 --> 00:03.162
Martin's been framed for murder.

00:03.163 --> 00:04.693
I convince him
to surrender to you.

00:04.694 --> 00:06.431
You protect Martin from the FBI.

00:06.621 --> 00:08.161
But what about you, Curtis?

00:08.162 --> 00:09.663
What brings you back to Prague?

00:09.829 --> 00:11.989
How much did my brother and I pay you?

00:11.990 --> 00:13.325
I will take care of it.

00:13.326 --> 00:14.954
Please, I beg you.

00:15.590 --> 00:17.953
Dmitry just saved my life.

00:18.704 --> 00:20.186
I don't remember my real father.

00:20.308 --> 00:22.322
You took care of me and my mum
after he died.

00:22.479 --> 00:23.844
Do you mind carrying
my backpack through?

00:23.845 --> 00:27.452
Kate's in trouble. She's on her way to Paris
with some kid who's gonna martyr himself.

00:27.453 --> 00:28.757
Watch the bumps, eh?

00:30.665 --> 00:34.622
_

00:36.890 --> 00:38.089
You still alive in there?

00:39.726 --> 00:41.259
Were you aiming for the bumps?

00:44.836 --> 00:46.814
All right, look, Paris
is about 300 clicks.

00:46.850 --> 00:49.484
We gotta ditch this car
and find us a new ride.

00:49.519 --> 00:51.602
Nina's gonna be on our
ass, so we gotta move.

00:51.604 --> 00:53.071
There's no "we."

00:54.454 --> 00:56.474
- What are you talking about?
- You got me across the border.

00:56.616 --> 00:59.011
I can get to Paris on my own.
I know where Kate's going.

00:59.941 --> 01:03.531
Martin, you got an address off your kid's
computer, and a hunch he's a terrorist.

01:03.583 --> 01:05.782
Maybe Kate's with him, maybe
she isn't, but the truth is

01:05.882 --> 01:07.315
you don't know what the
hell you're walking into.

01:07.453 --> 01:09.620
All the more reason you
should go home to your family.

01:09.622 --> 01:11.505
Get your life back together.

01:11.541 --> 01:13.924
They'll be plenty of time for that.

01:13.960 --> 01:15.876
- Well, if you get caught...
- I've already aided

01:15.928 --> 01:17.127
and abetted you, Martin.

01:17.129 --> 01:19.346
Too late to back out now.

01:20.295 --> 01:22.349
Look... we gotta stick
to the back roads.

01:22.807 --> 01:25.269
Not as many cameras. Less
chance for Nina to trace us.

01:25.304 --> 01:26.637
Let's go.

01:30.082 --> 01:31.490
_

01:31.500 --> 01:32.977
<i>HARDY: We got a passport hit.</i>

01:32.979 --> 01:34.395
Where?

01:34.447 --> 01:35.420
Calais.

01:35.558 --> 01:37.992
Tony Rice entered France 20 minutes ago.

01:38.141 --> 01:38.950
How'd we miss him?

01:39.128 --> 01:40.585
Rice is your guy. This is on you.

01:42.221 --> 01:45.230
(sighing): Okay. Tony had asked
us to pull a kid off a train.

01:45.376 --> 01:47.319
- At Martin's request.
- The kid was clean.

01:47.455 --> 01:48.909
Why go after him?

01:48.961 --> 01:50.878
We must have missed something.

01:50.913 --> 01:53.204
Why else would a guy wanted for capital
murder walk away from protection?

01:53.359 --> 01:55.856
All I care about is bringing them in
before this whole thing goes to hell.

01:57.347 --> 01:58.974
(inhales) Okay, we find Tony...

01:59.009 --> 02:00.087
we find Martin.

02:00.139 --> 02:03.509
Call the French police, tell them to flag
any stolen vehicles between Calais and Paris.

02:03.675 --> 02:06.560
Tony's smart... first thing he's
gonna do is switch up his ride.

02:06.596 --> 02:09.513
(engine clicking, then starting)

02:16.355 --> 02:18.856
(engine revving)

02:20.443 --> 02:21.859
(tires screech, engine revs)

02:24.645 --> 02:27.656
_

02:28.167 --> 02:29.833
(man praying in Arabic over P.A.)

02:31.000 --> 02:37.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

03:02.485 --> 03:04.234
<i>WOMAN: Thanks again for letting us stay.</i>

03:04.236 --> 03:06.203
You're very welcome.

03:06.238 --> 03:08.739
I told my students
about your demonstration.

03:08.741 --> 03:10.912
Some of them want to
come show their support.

03:11.057 --> 03:12.891
That's brilliant. Thank you.

03:13.034 --> 03:14.351
I've never been to Paris.

03:14.487 --> 03:17.616
We were hoping to do some sightseeing
before the protest tomorrow.

03:17.917 --> 03:19.416
Any suggestions?

03:20.008 --> 03:21.600
_

03:22.822 --> 03:24.204
Jamal tells me

03:24.240 --> 03:26.290
you just recently converted.

03:26.325 --> 03:28.993
May I ask how that came about?

03:31.497 --> 03:34.081
I found out my parents
were from Chechnya,

03:34.457 --> 03:37.751
but my Mum kept it secret.

03:37.803 --> 03:40.087
I realized my whole life was a lie.

03:40.139 --> 03:42.556
I make my own decisions now.

03:42.592 --> 03:44.258
What does your Mum think

03:44.310 --> 03:46.810
about the new path you've chosen?

03:46.846 --> 03:49.063
I don't really care.

03:49.098 --> 03:51.315
Well, the Holy Quran says

03:51.350 --> 03:53.970
"You should be kind to your parents,

03:54.022 --> 03:56.024
say not a word to them of contempt,

03:56.136 --> 03:57.425
not repel them,

03:57.726 --> 04:00.894
but address them in terms of honor."

04:04.399 --> 04:06.649
Isn't Ifti coming to breakfast?

04:33.895 --> 04:36.563
(high-pitched tone)

04:36.598 --> 04:38.598
(people screaming, shouting)

04:40.852 --> 04:41.768
(knocking on door)

04:41.770 --> 04:43.236
Ifti?

04:43.271 --> 04:44.664
Just a sec.

04:52.030 --> 04:53.363
What's keeping you?

04:53.415 --> 04:54.664
Nothing.

04:54.699 --> 04:56.366
I'm ready now.

05:01.018 --> 05:05.525
Sync and corrections by rickSG
www.addic7ed.com

05:06.062 --> 05:10.099
_

05:29.901 --> 05:32.318
Show me why I'm here.

05:42.998 --> 05:44.497
(groans)

05:45.517 --> 05:47.800
I put hidden compartments
in three trucks.

05:47.836 --> 05:50.253
More if you like.

05:51.807 --> 05:54.641
Depends on amount of
product you wish to move.

05:58.179 --> 05:59.960
Safer this way.

06:00.682 --> 06:02.599
Can you make them bigger?

06:02.651 --> 06:04.434
However big you need.

06:04.486 --> 06:08.321
Can you get trucks to Chechnya?

06:08.356 --> 06:10.240
I know who to pay,

06:10.275 --> 06:12.659
how much to get trucks over border.

06:14.579 --> 06:16.303
What are we moving?

06:16.781 --> 06:18.197
(chuckles)

06:18.199 --> 06:20.388
<i>MARTIN: AKs, RPGs.</i>

06:20.619 --> 06:21.918
We were right.

06:22.351 --> 06:25.204
Doku's selling drugs to buy weapons...

06:25.206 --> 06:28.124
Enough to arm an entire
brigade of Chechen rebels.

06:28.363 --> 06:31.544
Orders from General Arsanov, no doubt.

06:31.546 --> 06:33.880
How are things with Doku's brother?

06:33.882 --> 06:37.767
Ah, he keeps Tamir at arm's
length from the business.

06:37.802 --> 06:39.385
No intel to be gained from him.

06:39.387 --> 06:43.556
Well, befriending Tamir wasn't a
total waste of time... it got you in.

06:46.227 --> 06:47.977
I sent the boys shopping.

06:48.029 --> 06:49.228
(chuckles)

07:14.255 --> 07:15.672
(snapping fingers)

07:16.841 --> 07:18.224
Audio's good.

07:18.259 --> 07:19.926
Pull up a chair, old chap.

07:19.928 --> 07:21.894
Enjoy the show.

07:28.124 --> 07:32.392
_

07:32.857 --> 07:34.407
<i>RICE: Have you thought
about what you're gonna say</i>

07:34.442 --> 07:36.075
<i>to the girl when you find her?</i>

07:36.111 --> 07:38.077
The important thing is
to make sure she's safe.

07:45.120 --> 07:46.252
(tires squealing)

07:49.090 --> 07:50.289
(siren wailing)

07:51.960 --> 07:53.543
So much for the back roads.

07:56.965 --> 07:58.381
(tires squealing)

08:00.802 --> 08:03.636
(siren wailing)

08:07.475 --> 08:09.275
(siren wailing)

08:16.484 --> 08:18.162
- Hang on.
- I'm hanging.

08:20.989 --> 08:23.623
(police officer speaking
indistinctly over P.A.)

08:32.833 --> 08:35.333
(tires squeal, engine revs)

08:36.638 --> 08:38.471
(speaking French)

08:44.110 --> 08:47.436
_

08:48.576 --> 08:50.602
_

08:51.066 --> 08:54.487
_

08:54.563 --> 08:56.702
_

08:57.390 --> 09:01.793
_

09:06.481 --> 09:08.531
Come on, let's go home.

09:08.567 --> 09:10.567
Oh, my feet are killing me.

09:11.786 --> 09:13.144
The hell with these people!

09:13.277 --> 09:15.405
You shouldn't say "hell."

09:15.457 --> 09:18.074
18 months of knocking on doors,

09:18.126 --> 09:20.025
pounding the pavement, and
what do we have to show for it?

09:20.160 --> 09:22.495
I think I need new insoles.

09:22.497 --> 09:24.831
18 months, Hanson.

09:25.968 --> 09:27.887
We haven't baptise a single soul.

09:28.053 --> 09:29.074
What's the point?

09:29.240 --> 09:31.554
The work we're doing is holy.

09:31.590 --> 09:32.711
Have faith.

09:32.855 --> 09:35.508
WOMAN: Hey, Bible boys.

09:40.816 --> 09:42.682
Teach us how to pray.

09:42.718 --> 09:45.685
Yeah, we get down on our knees for you.

09:45.721 --> 09:47.020
(woman laughs)

09:47.055 --> 09:48.555
Let's go, Elder.

09:50.726 --> 09:52.299
Why are you both called Elder?

09:52.334 --> 09:53.193
It's a title.

09:53.228 --> 09:56.199
We give up our first names
for two years in the service of God.

09:56.231 --> 09:57.697
It's a pretty strict rule.

09:57.733 --> 09:59.733
And you follow all the rules...

10:02.704 --> 10:04.571
Elder Ballard?

10:07.743 --> 10:09.376
HANSON: Come on, Ballard.

10:09.411 --> 10:10.994
Ballard?

10:11.046 --> 10:12.612
Ballard!

10:17.029 --> 10:20.667
_

10:21.340 --> 10:23.089
Ballard?

10:24.343 --> 10:26.426
Ballard?

10:27.679 --> 10:29.012
Oh, I, uh,

10:29.064 --> 10:31.348
I told you, I don't drink coffee.

10:31.400 --> 10:33.733
It's a good thing I brought you cocoa.

10:33.769 --> 10:35.318
(chuckles)

10:35.354 --> 10:36.770
All right.

10:38.774 --> 10:41.741
You know there's the slightest
bit of caffeine in chocolate?

10:42.944 --> 10:44.194
Yeah.

10:44.246 --> 10:45.779
I walk on the wild side.

10:45.781 --> 10:48.415
(both laughing)

10:52.537 --> 10:54.788
He's ready for you in two.

10:54.790 --> 10:56.923
(chuckles)

10:58.116 --> 10:59.745
_

11:02.697 --> 11:05.090
_

