_

11:14.475 --> 11:16.552
_

11:17.415 --> 11:20.361
_

11:21.162 --> 11:24.798
_

11:24.799 --> 11:27.090
_

11:27.735 --> 11:29.339
_

11:30.794 --> 11:32.453
_

11:33.443 --> 11:35.948
_

11:36.139 --> 11:38.303
_

11:38.790 --> 11:40.206
What did he say?

11:40.258 --> 11:42.175
A man picked up Jaros from his bar.

11:42.210 --> 11:43.927
What man?

11:44.951 --> 11:46.346
We have a witness

11:46.381 --> 11:48.298
who saw you pick up Janic in a car.

11:48.300 --> 11:51.099
Who saw Dmitry beat
the crap out of Janic.

11:51.285 --> 11:54.013
Then, a few days later, we find
him with a hole in his head.

11:54.105 --> 11:55.388
So who pulled the trigger, Tamir?

11:55.440 --> 11:56.639
Was it Dmitry?

11:56.641 --> 11:58.441
Your brother? You?

12:00.562 --> 12:02.061
I-I tell you,

12:02.113 --> 12:03.646
I don't know.

12:09.404 --> 12:11.988
(keypad beeping, lock clicks)

12:18.246 --> 12:19.712
He's sweating like a pig.

12:19.748 --> 12:21.047
He's nervous.

12:21.082 --> 12:22.882
He's an addict.

12:22.918 --> 12:25.001
I say we let him get sick,

12:25.003 --> 12:26.886
then offer him some medicine.

12:26.922 --> 12:30.223
(chuckles) I'm not
giving drugs to a druggie.

12:30.258 --> 12:32.308
Do you want to nail Petrovich or not?

12:34.617 --> 12:36.049
_

12:36.084 --> 12:39.015
<i>HANSON: Give us strength to
overcome worldly temptation.</i>

12:39.017 --> 12:40.683
In the name of Jesus Christ.

12:41.029 --> 12:43.549
- Amen.
- Amen.

12:50.386 --> 12:52.529
Hanson.

12:52.531 --> 12:54.531
I've been thinking.

12:54.533 --> 12:56.199
Those girls,

12:56.201 --> 12:58.167
maybe there's a reason
we keep running into them.

12:58.203 --> 13:01.447
Maybe it's because they work
the same street corner every day?

13:01.540 --> 13:03.456
I think we can save them.

13:04.876 --> 13:06.463
They're prostitutes.

13:06.498 --> 13:08.699
So? I think their hearts are open to us.

13:08.842 --> 13:11.014
I think something of
theirs is open to us.

13:11.049 --> 13:12.549
Do you think they want to
be doing what they're doing?

13:12.551 --> 13:16.064
They do it because they're desperate,
sad and lost, and we can help them.

13:16.162 --> 13:18.471
We can show them the
way to a better life.

13:18.523 --> 13:20.306
You told me to have faith.

13:21.476 --> 13:23.192
Yeah.

13:30.518 --> 13:31.898
_

13:31.903 --> 13:33.453
<i>BLAZEK: We were reluctant.</i>

13:33.488 --> 13:35.655
<i>Working together, we
didn't want any gossip.</i>

13:35.707 --> 13:37.540
GABI: But it started anyway.

13:37.576 --> 13:39.292
So I thought, since everyone knew,

13:39.327 --> 13:41.494
why not make it official?

13:41.546 --> 13:43.880
He proposed on the Charles Bridge.

13:44.258 --> 13:46.082
Original, right?

13:46.084 --> 13:48.084
Yeah.

13:48.086 --> 13:50.253
Um...

13:50.255 --> 13:52.088
(clears throat) Gabi said on the phone

13:52.090 --> 13:54.641
you had some important
information for me

13:54.676 --> 13:56.426
about Dmitry Petrovich?

13:57.929 --> 14:01.314
The night you and Gabi
had Dmitry in custody,

14:01.349 --> 14:03.900
I got a call from Czech Intelligence.

14:03.935 --> 14:06.069
I was told to let him walk.

14:07.606 --> 14:10.106
They wouldn't give me
any details at the time,

14:10.108 --> 14:11.858
but I found out later that he was a part

14:11.910 --> 14:14.077
of a British operation.

14:14.112 --> 14:15.528
MI6.

14:15.580 --> 14:17.914
Dmitry was one of theirs.

14:20.418 --> 14:21.584
Did you know about this?

14:23.121 --> 14:24.704
He only told me last night.

14:24.756 --> 14:26.623
I'm sorry I couldn't
tell you at the time.

14:26.625 --> 14:28.925
I was following orders.

14:28.960 --> 14:31.628
I know what Dmitry did to you.

14:35.634 --> 14:37.300
(sighs)

14:44.726 --> 14:46.643
So what if he's working for Six?

14:46.645 --> 14:50.540
Doesn't change the fact that he's
a murderer and a drug smuggler,

14:50.705 --> 14:52.179
and he flaunted it!

14:57.973 --> 15:00.250
- What was the operation?
- I don't know.

15:00.388 --> 15:01.908
Who else was involved?

15:01.960 --> 15:03.376
I've told you everything.

15:03.411 --> 15:04.661
You sure about that?

15:04.663 --> 15:06.162
Curtis...

15:07.449 --> 15:10.430
The only reason I choose to tell
you, Ballard, is because I thought

15:11.010 --> 15:12.719
it will help you to move on.

15:13.364 --> 15:16.172
But do what you will.

15:16.174 --> 15:18.174
You always have.

15:24.599 --> 15:28.518
(door opens, closes)

15:31.297 --> 15:33.270
_

15:33.579 --> 15:35.095
<i>RICE: Get out the car.</i>

15:36.098 --> 15:37.135
What are you talking about?

15:37.310 --> 15:39.473
There's a better chance of
one of us making it to Paris

15:39.616 --> 15:41.371
- than both of us.
- Tony.

15:41.539 --> 15:43.188
Martin, the cops are
looking for this car.

15:43.355 --> 15:44.630
If I turn myself in,

15:44.806 --> 15:47.540
it'll put their focus on me long
enough for you to hop a train to Paris.

15:47.666 --> 15:49.751
- No.
- Give me your phone.

15:50.279 --> 15:51.247
Why?

15:51.480 --> 15:52.813
I'm giving you Nina's number.

15:52.815 --> 15:54.481
You get into a jam, you call her.

15:56.068 --> 15:57.317
She put the cops on us.

15:57.319 --> 15:59.453
She was just doing her job, Martin.

15:59.488 --> 16:00.904
She's one of the good ones.

16:00.956 --> 16:02.956
You can trust her.

16:04.827 --> 16:06.877
Thanks, Tony.

16:06.912 --> 16:08.829
For everything.

16:08.864 --> 16:12.082
You get to Paris and save the day.

16:12.134 --> 16:13.834
That's how you thank me.

16:37.912 --> 16:40.522
_

16:40.881 --> 16:42.235
_

16:45.164 --> 16:48.312
_

16:53.264 --> 16:54.753
_

16:55.135 --> 16:56.683
_

17:09.058 --> 17:10.773
(handcuffs clicking)

17:11.351 --> 17:13.060
<i>HARDY: Well, they have Tony.</i>

17:13.061 --> 17:15.229
What about Martin?

17:15.231 --> 17:16.864
(sighs)

17:18.534 --> 17:21.412
I'm sorry, Nina, but I'm gonna
have to get my chief involved.

17:23.204 --> 17:24.788
Let me talk to Tony.

17:24.839 --> 17:25.925
Give me 24 hours.

17:26.066 --> 17:29.582
If we don't find Martin, then we go
to our bosses with our hats in hand.

17:29.712 --> 17:31.545
But until then,

17:31.547 --> 17:33.314
man the hell up.

17:38.220 --> 17:40.721
(horse whinnying) BALLARD:
Look at this place.

17:40.723 --> 17:43.114
You've done really
well for yourself, Gabi.

17:44.727 --> 17:47.311
Great house,

17:47.363 --> 17:49.313
great job,

17:49.842 --> 17:51.899
and great husband.

17:56.658 --> 17:59.206
I'm sorry I didn't warn you.

17:59.241 --> 18:01.375
Blazek wanted to tell you in person.

18:01.851 --> 18:04.294
You've been married to
that guy for ten years.

18:04.330 --> 18:06.163
He never told you the truth?

18:07.347 --> 18:09.583
What else do you think
he isn't telling you?

18:09.585 --> 18:11.669
He was following orders.

18:11.967 --> 18:13.804
Yeah, so were the Nazis.

18:14.423 --> 18:17.558
Are you calling my husband a Nazi?

18:17.593 --> 18:18.958
(scoffs)

18:22.455 --> 18:24.748
I'm going to call you a cab.

18:25.046 --> 18:27.834
You're a good investigator, Gabi.

18:30.095 --> 18:33.256
You must know there's something
wrong with all of this.

18:41.456 --> 18:42.711
_

18:42.746 --> 18:44.748
<i>HANSON: Regardless of what
you've done in the past,</i>

18:44.886 --> 18:47.404
great blessings are available to you

18:47.439 --> 18:50.607
if you begin now to
live the law of chastity.

18:54.613 --> 18:56.246
Would you boys like a drink?

18:56.281 --> 18:58.532
Oh, um, no, thank you.

18:58.534 --> 19:00.500
Drinking is against our religion.

19:00.536 --> 19:01.686
I'll have a drink.

19:06.742 --> 19:08.458
Have you lost your mind?

19:08.494 --> 19:09.960
I can't take this anymore, Hanson.

19:09.995 --> 19:11.411
The preaching, the praying,

19:11.413 --> 19:13.997
the curfews, the rules...
We're 19 years old.

19:14.049 --> 19:15.415
We should be in college. We
should be going to parties.

19:15.417 --> 19:16.633
We should be getting laid.

19:16.669 --> 19:17.751
We should be leaving.

19:17.753 --> 19:19.136
I need this, Hanson.

19:19.171 --> 19:20.254
No, you don't.

19:35.271 --> 19:37.237
Ah.

19:37.273 --> 19:38.989
(chuckles)

19:39.024 --> 19:41.024
(sighs)

19:55.374 --> 19:57.624
Curtis...

20:07.219 --> 20:10.137
(sighs)

20:14.499 --> 20:16.276
So, uh,

20:16.312 --> 20:17.978
- do I...?
- You pay first.

20:25.154 --> 20:28.789
Uh, this is all I got.

20:31.746 --> 20:33.327
This will do.

20:38.250 --> 20:40.634
♪

21:00.105 --> 21:02.856
♪

21:17.172 --> 21:18.202
(sighs)

21:18.362 --> 21:20.331
_

21:20.430 --> 21:21.842
(Ballard sighs)

21:35.724 --> 21:39.026
(exhales)

22:08.724 --> 22:11.591
♪

22:26.064 --> 22:27.994
_

22:28.079 --> 22:30.212
<i>FARRAH: Aw, you two
are so cute together.</i>

22:30.248 --> 22:32.081
(phone clicks)

22:34.085 --> 22:35.334
(Farrah giggles)

22:35.386 --> 22:36.385
(phone buzzes)

22:36.420 --> 22:38.003
FARRAH: Uh-oh.

22:38.055 --> 22:39.672
Parent police.

22:48.933 --> 22:51.150
ILYANA: Kate, please call me.

22:51.185 --> 22:53.652
I don't want to fight, I just
want to know you are okay.

22:53.688 --> 22:55.237
I love you.

22:58.442 --> 23:00.526
Everything okay?

23:00.578 --> 23:03.195
Want to go for a walk?

23:03.247 --> 23:04.697
Sure.

23:05.654 --> 23:07.338
<i>KATE: Maybe I should call my mum.</i>

23:07.451 --> 23:09.418
She'll only make you feel worse.

23:09.453 --> 23:11.186
You're doing what you should be doing,

23:11.222 --> 23:12.538
following your spiritual calling.

23:13.233 --> 23:14.997
You're embracing your faith.

23:26.387 --> 23:28.721
(giggles)

23:29.596 --> 23:31.106
Why are you laughing?

23:31.142 --> 23:33.809
Just wasn't expecting you
to eat my face off like that.

23:35.613 --> 23:36.812
It's okay.

23:37.323 --> 23:39.114
I liked it.

23:39.562 --> 23:41.008
We should get married.

23:45.217 --> 23:46.705
You're serious?

23:47.305 --> 23:49.208
Before the protest tomorrow.

23:49.243 --> 23:50.492
Let's get married.

23:51.746 --> 23:54.463
Look, Ifti, I really like you, but...

23:54.498 --> 23:55.965
I'm barely 18.

23:56.000 --> 23:58.050
I-I don't want to get married.

23:58.456 --> 24:00.753
Can't we just have some fun?

24:00.805 --> 24:03.055
You're filling my mind
with unholy thoughts.

24:03.090 --> 24:05.057
It's okay to have the hots for someone.

24:05.092 --> 24:06.342
It's not a bad thing.

24:07.946 --> 24:10.896
- I'm glad you feel that way about me.
- Look, I said we can't.

24:11.154 --> 24:13.849
- I know our religion says...
- "Our religion"?

24:13.851 --> 24:15.187
What, you think you
can put on a headscarf

24:15.354 --> 24:17.171
and go to a mosque a few
times and you're a Muslim?

24:18.773 --> 24:20.356
Why are you acting like this?

24:20.408 --> 24:22.024
You're a slag.

24:28.366 --> 24:29.999
<i>KATE: He's like Jekyll and Hyde.</i>

24:30.034 --> 24:31.750
One minute, he's this sweet guy,

24:31.786 --> 24:33.803
the next minute, he's calling me a slag.

24:33.905 --> 24:35.308
I shouldn't have kissed him,

24:35.343 --> 24:37.006
that doesn't give him the
right to treat me like dirt.

24:37.041 --> 24:37.874
FARRAH: Of course it doesn't.

24:37.926 --> 24:40.092
But you have to understand,
Ifti's not a typical boy.

24:40.127 --> 24:41.927
He's a devout Muslim.

24:41.963 --> 24:43.629
He definitely fancies you,

24:43.681 --> 24:45.347
but he can't do anything about it.

24:45.383 --> 24:47.099
Can you imagine how
frustrating that would be?

24:47.134 --> 24:48.771
Yeah, it's definitely frustrating.

24:48.936 --> 24:51.136
So of course he's gonna
get down on one knee.

24:51.188 --> 24:52.919
It's the only way he
can get you into bed.

24:52.954 --> 24:55.691
But he should not
have called you a slag.

24:55.726 --> 24:57.559
I'm definitely gonna take
the piss out of him for that.

25:03.465 --> 25:06.102
_

25:11.709 --> 25:12.741
Watch the wife.

25:37.685 --> 25:40.519
I'm going to the market.

25:40.571 --> 25:42.938
Not without covering your head.

25:42.940 --> 25:45.190
If you want to leave this house,

25:45.242 --> 25:47.192
you will wear your hijab.

25:56.587 --> 25:58.170
I'm sorry, Doku, no.

25:58.205 --> 25:59.762
I don't like what it represents

25:59.898 --> 26:02.007
or the man you are becoming.

26:02.767 --> 26:05.127
And what...

26:05.129 --> 26:07.463
kind of man is that?

26:11.385 --> 26:13.052
You've become strict and narrow.

26:13.861 --> 26:16.250
We left Chechnya for a better life.

26:16.390 --> 26:18.255
To raise children in freedom.

26:18.290 --> 26:21.393
And now we see that the
world we have come to

26:21.445 --> 26:23.479
is vile and corrupt.

26:23.481 --> 26:25.731
We need to protect our daughter.

26:25.783 --> 26:26.982
And you

26:26.984 --> 26:28.958
need to set an example.

26:29.123 --> 26:32.444
I don't want our daughter growing
up thinking she's less than a man.

26:32.740 --> 26:34.623
That she has to hide her face,

26:34.658 --> 26:36.992
that she cannot have her
own thoughts and dreams.

26:40.831 --> 26:43.332
(Ilyana sobbing)

26:43.334 --> 26:45.000
He's a charmer.

26:47.505 --> 26:49.505
I don't want to be here anymore.

26:49.507 --> 26:52.341
I'm going to leave and
I'm taking Katya with me!

26:54.512 --> 26:56.512
I'll kill you

26:56.514 --> 26:58.313
if you take her away from me.

27:09.944 --> 27:11.160
You will

27:11.195 --> 27:13.779
wear your headscarf

27:13.831 --> 27:16.198
when you leave this house.

27:28.012 --> 27:29.711
<i>MARTIN: She's our in.</i>

27:29.713 --> 27:31.847
<i>She wants to leave her husband.</i>

27:31.882 --> 27:33.057
She's perfect.

27:33.197 --> 27:34.933
But is she up to the task?

27:34.969 --> 27:37.219
She's ready to do anything
to save her daughter.

27:37.889 --> 27:39.818
Even spy on her husband?

27:39.980 --> 27:42.191
Doku's planning to move an arsenal

27:42.226 --> 27:44.359
and we're nowhere near
finding the general.

27:44.395 --> 27:46.979
If there's a chance this woman
can get us some information,

27:47.031 --> 27:48.363
then we need to take it.

27:48.399 --> 27:50.499
If he finds out,

27:50.534 --> 27:52.568
he will most certainly kill her.

27:55.372 --> 27:57.239
Can you live with that?

27:59.076 --> 28:00.742
<i>(fist pounding)</i>

28:00.744 --> 28:02.744
(panting)

28:04.381 --> 28:07.082
(lock keypad beeping)

28:17.595 --> 28:18.927
GABI: Tamir...

28:20.681 --> 28:22.564
I want to help you.

28:22.600 --> 28:26.101
But first, you need to help us.

28:28.522 --> 28:30.272
Who killed Jaros?

28:32.776 --> 28:35.777
Who killed Jaros?

28:35.779 --> 28:37.946
I don't know.

28:37.948 --> 28:39.498
I think you do know.

28:39.533 --> 28:41.033
Tell us, Tamir.

28:41.085 --> 28:43.118
You don't have to suffer.

28:44.538 --> 28:46.004
Dmitry...

28:46.040 --> 28:48.540
Dmitry killed Jaros?

28:48.592 --> 28:49.791
TAMIR: Not Jaros...

28:49.793 --> 28:51.426
other guy.

28:51.462 --> 28:54.463
He shot him right in front of me.

28:55.799 --> 28:56.932
I swear.

28:56.967 --> 28:59.468
Now, I helped you, yes?

29:01.639 --> 29:03.939
Not until you answer
some more questions.

29:09.764 --> 29:12.584
_

29:13.134 --> 29:15.317
Let's go.

29:17.988 --> 29:20.405
You did not pay for Toma.

29:20.457 --> 29:21.657
Yeah, we didn't do anything.

29:21.659 --> 29:23.029
OKSANA: You pay for her time.

29:23.127 --> 29:25.094
- You've got to be kidding me.
- Just pay her, Hanson.

29:25.129 --> 29:26.345
No, I'm not paying for a whore.

29:26.380 --> 29:27.629
Just pay her, goddamn it!

29:36.891 --> 29:38.357
I don't have any money.

29:38.392 --> 29:39.942
You cannot pay?

29:40.462 --> 29:43.478
- We'll go to an ATM.
- What? No. They're robbing us.

29:45.093 --> 29:46.889
_

29:46.924 --> 29:47.983
Come on!

29:48.170 --> 29:50.439
_

29:55.493 --> 29:57.493
Come back, you bastards!

29:59.797 --> 30:02.164
Ow! Ow, ow, ow. Ow. Hey, Elder, stop.

30:02.166 --> 30:03.749
I think one of my blisters popped.

30:03.801 --> 30:05.000
Hanson, we gotta go.

30:05.036 --> 30:07.419
MAN: Bible Boys! That's you, yes?

30:07.471 --> 30:10.005
Why you no pay my girls?

30:10.446 --> 30:13.559
Listen, this is just
a big misunderstanding.

30:13.594 --> 30:14.843
Okay?

30:15.763 --> 30:17.179
Oh!

30:17.181 --> 30:18.833
I want my money.

30:18.834 --> 30:19.885
HANSON: Leave him alone!

30:19.920 --> 30:21.066
Hanson!

30:21.102 --> 30:23.485
(grunts)

30:23.521 --> 30:25.771
(groaning)

30:27.525 --> 30:29.525
(engine revs, tires squeal)

30:30.216 --> 30:32.028
_

30:32.696 --> 30:34.696
(Hanson coughs)

30:34.698 --> 30:35.998
(Ballard shouts in Lithuanian)

30:39.420 --> 30:41.170
Heavenly Father,
please don't punish him,

30:41.205 --> 30:42.921
it wasn't his fault, it was mine.

30:42.957 --> 30:45.090
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

30:45.126 --> 30:46.542
(crying): I'm sorry.

30:46.544 --> 30:48.293
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

30:48.345 --> 30:49.628
I'm sorry...

30:52.483 --> 30:54.360
_

30:54.990 --> 30:56.190
<i>(sharp knocking at door)</i>

30:56.225 --> 30:58.559
(Ballard grunts sleepily)

31:00.813 --> 31:03.530
(knocking continues)

31:13.659 --> 31:15.409
What do you want?

31:18.081 --> 31:21.231
These are the case files from
the Dmitry investigation...

31:21.368 --> 31:23.803
Everything we compiled back in 2001.

31:24.003 --> 31:26.637
Surveillance photos and
logs, arrest reports...

31:26.673 --> 31:28.180
also, Krystof's reports,

31:28.316 --> 31:31.676
and everything else that was
gathered after we were off the case.

31:31.711 --> 31:33.477
I dug them out of storage last night.

31:33.513 --> 31:34.729
It was cold

31:34.764 --> 31:35.980
and smelly down there,

31:36.015 --> 31:37.598
so I hope you appreciate this.

31:39.936 --> 31:42.820
Listen, I'm sorry about yesterday.

31:42.855 --> 31:44.071
I was, um...

31:44.107 --> 31:45.773
A prick?

31:47.443 --> 31:49.076
(wry laugh)

31:52.749 --> 31:54.498
I assume you drink coffee now?

31:55.044 --> 31:56.784
Oh, hell, yes.

32:03.124 --> 32:06.301
_

32:07.101 --> 32:08.424
<i>RICE: Thanks for getting me out.</i>

32:08.459 --> 32:09.513
<i>NINA: Yeah, sure.</i>

32:09.549 --> 32:10.715
Now, where's Martin?

32:11.011 --> 32:12.951
The deal we made with
Six to protect him...

32:13.284 --> 32:14.316
That still stand?

32:14.351 --> 32:17.054
Tell me where I can find him,
and I'll do everything I can.

32:17.490 --> 32:19.198
All right, like I said,

32:19.233 --> 32:21.442
Martin thinks this kid
Ifti's gonna martyr himself.

32:21.477 --> 32:23.641
Any idea how, where, when?

32:23.976 --> 32:25.546
All he's got is some address in Paris.

32:25.548 --> 32:27.381
And that's where he's
going... look, Nina,

32:27.383 --> 32:28.908
if Martin's convinced that
something big is gonna happen,

32:28.985 --> 32:30.294
then we are wasting our time here, okay?

32:30.470 --> 32:32.352
- We gotta go help him.
- Tony...

32:33.489 --> 32:34.888
There's no "we."

32:36.192 --> 32:38.225
You know, that's the second time
in the last two days I've heard that.

32:38.375 --> 32:40.111
Maybe you should've
listened the first time.

32:40.563 --> 32:42.613
I'm coming with you. Let's go.

32:42.648 --> 32:44.982
The French police called the FBI

32:45.034 --> 32:47.201
when they checked out your credentials.

32:48.871 --> 32:50.904
They're sending you back to the States.

32:52.999 --> 32:54.405
I'm sorry.

32:58.805 --> 33:00.752
Make sure it wasn't all for nothing.

33:01.083 --> 33:02.749
And I'm sorry if...

33:02.751 --> 33:04.585
if I got you in trouble.

33:06.222 --> 33:08.222
You were always trouble.

33:11.760 --> 33:14.478
Tell me where to find Martin.

33:14.513 --> 33:16.180
(locomotive horn blaring)

33:21.103 --> 33:23.770
(brakes squeaking)

33:33.941 --> 33:36.714
_

33:37.035 --> 33:39.688
_

33:39.784 --> 33:42.818
_

33:43.178 --> 33:46.808
_

33:46.996 --> 33:50.561
_

33:50.562 --> 33:52.484
_

33:52.743 --> 33:54.250
_

33:54.695 --> 33:56.118
_

33:56.379 --> 33:57.543
_

33:57.806 --> 33:58.889
(group agreeing in French)

34:08.817 --> 34:10.484
You weren't at breakfast again.

34:10.838 --> 34:12.474
I was taking a walk.

34:19.911 --> 34:21.628
I was cruel to you.

34:21.664 --> 34:23.630
I see that now.

34:23.666 --> 34:25.666
I'm sorry.

34:25.668 --> 34:27.333
Please forgive me.

34:27.335 --> 34:29.253
Of course.

34:29.304 --> 34:30.587
(car horn honking)

34:31.679 --> 34:33.757
Talk about it after?

34:33.809 --> 34:36.176
Sure, after.

34:48.190 --> 34:49.906
I'm, uh, I'm looking for Kate Crawford.

34:49.942 --> 34:50.857
Is she here?

34:50.859 --> 34:53.243
Who are you?

34:53.279 --> 34:54.911
Her stepfather.

34:54.947 --> 34:56.530
Kate's not here right now.

34:56.532 --> 34:58.832
Would you like to come in?

35:00.669 --> 35:01.868
Thank you.

35:03.846 --> 35:06.006
I was supposed to meet her,
but she never turned up.

35:06.041 --> 35:08.008
I was, I was worried.

35:08.043 --> 35:10.177
Meet her where?

35:10.212 --> 35:12.512
Is she with, uh, Ifti?

35:12.548 --> 35:14.848
She never mentioned a stepfather.

35:15.336 --> 35:17.634
Look, I've...

35:17.686 --> 35:19.636
I used to be very close to her.

35:19.688 --> 35:21.521
And, uh, I've been away for a long time.

35:21.557 --> 35:23.273
She's very important to me.

35:23.309 --> 35:24.941
Please, if you know where she is...

35:24.977 --> 35:27.311
She's at the protest.

35:27.363 --> 35:29.112
What protest?

35:29.148 --> 35:30.647
At the school.

35:30.699 --> 35:32.866
Well, what's it about?

35:32.901 --> 35:34.507
The anti-Islamic laws

35:34.671 --> 35:36.389
that persecute us for our beliefs.

35:37.072 --> 35:39.072
Do you have a car?

35:39.074 --> 35:40.230
Yes, why?

35:40.394 --> 35:41.936
We need to get to the school now.

35:42.078 --> 35:43.817
- Call the police.
- Yeah, what's going on?!

35:43.955 --> 35:45.225
It's a peaceful protest.

35:45.351 --> 35:48.382
Tell them a boy at the school
is gonna martyr himself.

35:52.221 --> 35:54.588
<i>(protestors chanting)</i>

35:56.304 --> 35:57.933
_

35:58.090 --> 36:00.479
_

36:00.480 --> 36:02.479
_

36:02.480 --> 36:04.633
_

36:07.519 --> 36:11.438
(chanting continues)

36:16.278 --> 36:20.364
(chanting continues)

36:27.460 --> 36:31.211
_

36:31.212 --> 36:33.305
_

36:33.306 --> 36:36.791
_

36:36.792 --> 36:39.490
_

36:39.491 --> 36:41.932
_

36:42.744 --> 36:45.293
_

36:45.474 --> 36:49.411
_

36:50.001 --> 36:51.250
Hey, piss off!

36:51.252 --> 36:52.718
YOUNG IMAM: Oh, no, no, no, no!

36:52.719 --> 36:54.179
_

36:54.180 --> 36:55.997
_

36:57.258 --> 36:59.592
(all shouting)

36:59.594 --> 37:02.428
(siren approaching)

37:04.932 --> 37:06.232
Leave her alone!

37:06.267 --> 37:07.817
No, no, no, no, no, no!

37:07.852 --> 37:09.935
Hey! Hey! Hey! Hey!

37:09.937 --> 37:11.237
(indistinct shouting)

37:11.272 --> 37:13.105
(screaming, clamoring)

37:19.530 --> 37:20.780
(tires screech)

37:23.701 --> 37:25.284
♪

37:27.872 --> 37:30.206
(clicks, whines)

37:30.258 --> 37:31.624
(police speaking
French over loudspeaker)

37:31.626 --> 37:34.237
Kate! Kate Crawford!

37:34.272 --> 37:36.796
Kate!

37:38.549 --> 37:41.300
(crowd chanting, clamoring)

37:44.032 --> 37:45.805
<i>Allahu Akbar!</i>

37:45.807 --> 37:47.807
(woman screams)

37:49.477 --> 37:50.939
(crowd screaming, clamoring)

37:51.095 --> 37:54.980
♪ Everybody has to fly

37:57.087 --> 37:59.880
♪ Everybody

37:59.915 --> 38:04.073
♪ Has to fly

38:04.125 --> 38:06.492
♪ Everybody

38:06.494 --> 38:09.211
♪ Has to fly...

38:09.247 --> 38:11.080
(crowd clamoring)

38:13.680 --> 38:14.932
Kate?

38:14.967 --> 38:15.968
Are you hurt?

38:16.003 --> 38:17.670
(police whistle blowing)

38:17.672 --> 38:18.971
(crying)

38:19.006 --> 38:20.194
Hey, you're bleeding.

38:20.229 --> 38:21.390
It's all my fault.

38:22.643 --> 38:24.776
No. Come on...

38:24.811 --> 38:27.346
(siren wailing)

38:31.519 --> 38:33.402
(engine revs, tires screech)

38:33.438 --> 38:35.187
(siren wailing in distance)

38:40.871 --> 38:43.140
_

38:43.175 --> 38:44.606
<i>YOUNG BALLARD: It's all my fault.</i>

38:46.396 --> 38:49.067
If only I'd believed
in the mission more.

38:49.103 --> 38:51.820
It's not your fault Hanson died.

38:51.856 --> 38:53.489
It was a mugging.

38:53.524 --> 38:56.241
It was a random crime.

38:56.277 --> 38:58.610
God gave us free will, Elder.

38:58.612 --> 39:01.830
That means, unfortunately,
bad people do bad things.

39:01.866 --> 39:04.249
And sometimes they get away with it.

39:04.285 --> 39:06.585
Are the police still looking for him?

39:06.620 --> 39:08.170
The man who killed Hanson?

39:08.205 --> 39:10.873
True justice

39:10.925 --> 39:13.125
will be served in the next life.

39:16.130 --> 39:17.713
I've been thinking.

39:19.800 --> 39:22.634
I want to be an instrument
for justice in this life.

39:36.400 --> 39:37.733
(door closes)

39:44.828 --> 39:48.133
_

39:56.304 --> 39:59.317
_

40:02.176 --> 40:03.976
(indistinct chatter)

40:11.429 --> 40:12.818
May I help?

40:17.274 --> 40:19.024
Uh, uh...

40:19.026 --> 40:20.525
Thank you.

40:25.706 --> 40:27.065
I fell in the kitchen.

40:30.091 --> 40:31.503
What's her name?

40:31.941 --> 40:33.288
Katya.

40:33.729 --> 40:34.883
Hello, Katya.

40:36.393 --> 40:37.610
You like ice cream?

40:37.878 --> 40:39.378
(speaks Czech) Mm-hmm.

40:44.635 --> 40:47.219
(Martin speaks Czech) please.

40:49.306 --> 40:51.306
Thank you.

40:56.563 --> 40:58.480
(laughs)

41:00.601 --> 41:02.284
You like?

41:02.319 --> 41:03.785
(Katya speaks Czech)

41:03.821 --> 41:05.570
I think you've made a friend.

41:05.572 --> 41:07.656
(laughs)

41:13.341 --> 41:15.080
Stay down.

41:17.668 --> 41:19.067
Put pressure on it.

